def minWindow(s, t):
    from collections import Counter, defaultdict
    
    if not s or not t:
        return ''
    
    # Dictionary to keep count of characters in t
    dict_t = Counter(t)
    required = len(dict_t)
    
    # Left and right pointers
    left = right = 0
    
    # Formed is used to keep track of how many unique characters in the current window
    # have the desired frequency in t
    formed = 0
    
    # Dictionary to keep count of characters in current window
    window_counts = defaultdict(int)
    
    # ans tuple of the form (window length, left, right)
    ans = float('inf'), None, None
    
    while right < len(s):
        # Add one character from the right to the window
        character = s[right]
        window_counts[character] += 1
        
        # If this character's frequency matches the desired count in t, increment formed
        if character in dict_t and window_counts[character] == dict_t[character]:
            formed += 1
        
        # Try to contract the window
        while left <= right and formed == required:
            character = s[left]
            
            # Save the smallest window
            if right - left + 1 < ans[0]:
                ans = (right - left + 1, left, right)
            
            # Remove from the left of the window
            window_counts[character] -= 1
            if character in dict_t and window_counts[character] < dict_t[character]:
                formed -= 1
            
            left += 1
        
        right += 1
    
    return '' if ans[0] == float('inf') else s[ans[1]:ans[2] + 1]
